# 🔍 Portfolio Main-Thread Performance Audit

> **Objective:** Identify every blocking operation on the main thread that causes UI lag, shaking, or screen freezing — and prescribe a fix for each.

---

## Executive Summary

After a deep-dive through **every component** in the portfolio, I've identified **12 concrete main-thread blockers** ranked by severity. The good news: **none require an architectural rewrite**. Most are fixable with targeted optimizations (memoization, passive listeners, GPU offloading, and async scheduling).

---

## 🔴 Critical Blockers (High Impact on Jank)

### 1. `SkillIcon` — Infinite Framer-Motion Keyframe Per Icon (~20+ simultaneous)

**File:** [SkillsSection.tsx](file:///home/rocky/Projects/portfolio/components/portfolio/SkillsSection.tsx#L177-L208)

**Problem:** Each `SkillIcon` runs its own **infinite `y` keyframe animation** via Framer Motion. With 3 shape groups × ~8 icons each = **~24 independent JS-driven animation loops** running simultaneously. Framer Motion's `animate` prop with `repeat: Infinity` schedules a new `requestAnimationFrame` callback *per animated value per component*. This overwhelms the main thread.

**Why it causes shaking/freezing:**
- Each SkillIcon has its own float delay + float animation
- The parent `ShapeGroup` ALSO has its own infinite `y + rotate` animation (line 339-355)
- That's ~24 child animations + 3 parent animations = **~27 concurrent JS animation loops**

**Fix:**
```diff
- // CURRENT: JS-driven infinite animation per icon
- animate={isBuilt ? { y: [y, y - 8, y], opacity: 1, scale: 1 } : ...}
- transition={{ y: { duration: FLOAT_DURATION, repeat: Infinity, ... } }}

+ // FIX: Use CSS animation instead — zero JS cost
+ animate={isBuilt ? { opacity: 1, scale: 1 } : { scale: 0, opacity: 0 }}
+ className={`absolute z-10 ${isBuilt ? 'animate-float' : ''}`}
+ style={{ animationDelay: `${floatDelay}s` }}
```

Add to `globals.css`:
```css
@keyframes float {
  0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0); }
  50% { transform: translateY(-8px); }
}
.animate-float {
  animation: float 8s ease-in-out infinite;
  will-change: transform;
}
```

**Do the same for `ShapeGroup`'s parent container float animation** (line 339-355) — convert to CSS.

> **Impact: 🔥 HIGHEST — eliminates ~27 JS animation loops from main thread**

---

### 2. `HeroSection` — Unbounded `mousemove` Listener (fires 60+ times/sec)

**File:** [HeroSection.tsx](file:///home/rocky/Projects/portfolio/components/portfolio/HeroSection.tsx#L189-L198)

**Problem:** A raw `window.addEventListener("mousemove", ...)` fires on **every mouse move** (60-120 times/sec). Each callback does `getBoundingClientRect()` (forces layout recalc) + sets two MotionValues. Combined with the spring transforms on the image, this creates continuous layout thrashing.

**Fix:**
```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  let rafId: number | null = null;
  
  const handleMouse = (e: MouseEvent) => {
    if (rafId !== null) return; // Throttle to 1 per frame
    rafId = requestAnimationFrame(() => {
      const rect = containerRef.current?.getBoundingClientRect();
      if (!rect) { rafId = null; return; }
      mouseX.set(e.clientX - rect.width / 2);
      mouseY.set(e.clientY - rect.height / 2);
      rafId = null;
    });
  };
  
  window.addEventListener("mousemove", handleMouse, { passive: true });
  return () => {
    window.removeEventListener("mousemove", handleMouse);
    if (rafId !== null) cancelAnimationFrame(rafId);
  };
}, [mouseX, mouseY]);
```

> **Impact: Eliminates layout thrashing on every mouse move**

---

### 3. `PlatformCard` — 3D Transform + Spotlight on Every Mouse Move (×3 cards)

**File:** [PlatformCard.tsx](file:///home/rocky/Projects/portfolio/components/portfolio/ProblemSolving/PlatformCard.tsx#L72-L81)

**Problem:** Each PlatformCard runs `handleMouseMove` on every pixel move, calling `getBoundingClientRect()` + setting 2 MotionValues that drive 2 springs (`springRotateX`, `springRotateY`) + a `useTransform` for spotlight gradient. With **3 cards visible**, this is 3× the work on the main thread.

**Fix:** Same RAF-throttle pattern as #2. Also, add `{ passive: true }` to any mouse listeners.

---

### 4. `ContactSection` — `setInterval` Clock at 1000ms with React Re-render

**File:** [ContactSection.tsx](file:///home/rocky/Projects/portfolio/components/portfolio/ContactSection.tsx#L27-L38)

**Problem:** The `setInterval` runs **every 1 second** and calls `setCurrentTime(...)` which triggers a **full component re-render of the entire ContactSection** (424 lines of JSX + Framer Motion). This re-render includes re-evaluating `useMotionTemplate` (line 121), all AnimatePresence blocks, and the spotlight gradient.

**Fix:**
```tsx
// Extract clock into its own memoized component to isolate re-renders
function LiveClock() {
  const [currentTime, setCurrentTime] = useState("");
  
  useEffect(() => {
    const timer = setInterval(() => {
      setCurrentTime(new Intl.DateTimeFormat("en-US", {
        timeZone: "Asia/Dhaka", hour: "2-digit", minute: "2-digit", hour12: true,
      }).format(new Date()));
    }, 1000);
    return () => clearInterval(timer);
  }, []);
  
  return <span className="text-xs font-mono text-muted-foreground/60">Local Time: {currentTime || "--:-- --"}</span>;
}
```

Then use `<LiveClock />` inline — this isolates the 1s re-render to a **tiny leaf component** instead of re-rendering the entire ContactSection.

> **Impact: Prevents full 424-line component re-render every second**

---

### 5. `Preloader` — `setInterval` at 100ms with setState

**File:** [Preloader.tsx](file:///home/rocky/Projects/portfolio/components/portfolio/Preloader.tsx#L24-L34)

**Problem:** The progress simulation runs `setInterval` at **100ms** (10 re-renders/second), each calling `setProgress(...)`. Each re-render also triggers Framer Motion to recalculate the progress bar width animation (line 151).

**Fix:** Use `requestAnimationFrame` + a ref to track progress, only flushing to state when the visual difference is ≥1%:
```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  const progressRef = { current: 0 };
  let lastRendered = 0;
  let rafId: number;
  
  const tick = () => {
    if (progressRef.current >= 100) return;
    const increment = progressRef.current < 70 ? Math.random() * 2 : Math.random() * 0.3;
    progressRef.current = Math.min(progressRef.current + increment, 100);
    
    if (Math.round(progressRef.current) !== lastRendered) {
      lastRendered = Math.round(progressRef.current);
      setProgress(lastRendered);
    }
    
    rafId = requestAnimationFrame(tick);
  };
  rafId = requestAnimationFrame(tick);
  return () => cancelAnimationFrame(rafId);
}, []);
```

