| 12 | HeatmapCell → React.memo | 3 min | ⚡ Scroll perf |

---

## Can We Solve These With Async?

**Short answer: Not exactly.** These aren't async/await problems — they're **per-frame synchronous workload** problems. The main thread is overloaded with too many simultaneous animations and event handlers competing for the same 16ms frame budget.

The correct solutions are:

| Pattern | When to Use |
|---------|-------------|
| **CSS animations** (not JS) | For all infinite/decorative animations (floating, pulsing, marquees) |
| **RAF throttling** | For high-frequency event handlers (mousemove, scroll, resize) |
| **Component isolation** | For state updates that shouldn't re-render parent trees (clock, counters) |
| **GPU compositing** (`will-change`, `transform`, `contain`) | For expensive visual effects (blur, backdrop-filter) |
| **Single animation driver** (GSAP ticker driving Lenis) | When multiple animation systems compete for RAF |
| **`useMemo` / `React.memo`** | For expensive computations that re-run on every render |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The #1 root cause of the UI shaking is likely the **Lenis + independent RAF loop** (#8) combined with **~27 simultaneous JS-driven Framer Motion animation loops** (#1). Fixing these two alone should eliminate most visible jank.

